  <h1>JusticeFusion – Technical Whitepaper</h1>
  <p>JusticeFusion is a legal AI assistant designed for local legal sources, private documents and everyday legal research workflows in Bosnian, Croatian and Serbian. The system uses a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approach: before generating an answer, it first retrieves relevant parts of laws, regulations, case law, contracts, decisions or other documents, and then uses that context to produce a grounded response.</p>
  <p>The goal of JusticeFusion is not to replace lawyers, notaries, legal officers or other qualified professionals. Its purpose is to speed up legal research, reduce time spent searching through documents and assist in preparing drafts of answers, letters and other documents that can then be reviewed by a professional.</p>
  <h2>1. System overview</h2><p>JusticeFusion is a modular AI system built around several connected layers: user interface, document processing, embedding and indexing, retrieval, LLM generation and answer review. This architecture allows the system to be adapted for law firms, notary offices, corporate legal departments, public institutions and organizations that work with large volumes of regulations and internal documents.</p>
  <ul><li>SaaS,</li><li>private cloud,</li><li>on-premise installation on the client’s infrastructure,</li><li>local/offline installation.</li></ul>
  <h2>2. Core workflow</h2><ul><li>the user asks a question or uploads a document,</li><li>the system extracts text from PDF, DOCX, text files or images,</li><li>the document is cleaned, split and converted into embeddings,</li><li>the retrieval layer finds relevant parts of user documents and/or legal databases,</li><li>the LLM generates an answer based on retrieved context,</li><li>an additional review layer analyzes answer quality,</li><li>the user receives an answer and, when needed, a draft for expert editing.</li></ul>
  <h2>3–18. Key components and usage</h2>
  <p>JusticeFusion supports PDF, DOCX, text files, scanned documents and images in Latin and Cyrillic scripts. OCR, text cleaning and segmentation improve retrieval precision. The RAG architecture, hybrid retrieval (vector search, keyword search, BM25/TF-IDF) and embedding/indexing layer keep outputs closer to source material and reduce manual research effort.</p>
  <p>The system combines legal databases (laws, regulations, case law) with user documents (contracts, decisions, letters, internal acts). In advanced configurations it can use graph-aware retrieval to connect legal entities and relationships. After the first answer, an automatic review pipeline can perform iterative answer refinement through additional retrieval when needed.</p>
  <p>JusticeFusion can generate drafts (appeals, requests, official letters, contracts and other documents) and optionally export to DOCX. Such output should be treated as a draft ready for expert review. Deployment can be local, private cloud, controlled SaaS or offline, with access control, audit logging and local storage options depending on configuration.</p>
  <p>The interface is designed for legal teams: document upload, question history, source preview and answer export. Integrations can include DMS/ERP/CRM systems, legal databases, API and webhook workflows. A typical technology layer may include Python backend, Streamlit, SentenceTransformers, FAISS/Weaviate, SQLite/LMDB, OCR tools and local LLMs (e.g., via Ollama), with optional external providers when permitted.</p>
  <p>JusticeFusion is a support tool: it assists research, summarization and draft preparation, while final legal judgment and submission remain the responsibility of qualified professionals. Its value is faster, safer and more structured legal knowledge use while keeping control over confidential data.</p>
